===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.|en}} {{m|la|lithium}}, from {{m|la|lithia}} (in reference to Ancient Greek {{m|grc|λίθος||stone}}) + {{m|la|-ium}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈlɪθi.əm/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-us-lithium.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The simplest [[alkali]] [[metal]], the lightest solid element, and the third lightest chemical element (''symbol'' Li) with an [[atomic number]] of 3.
# {{lb|en|pharmaceutical drug|uncountable}} [[lithium carbonate|Lithium carbonate]] or other preparations of lithium metal used to treat [[manic depression]] and [[bipolar disorder]]s.
# A [[lithium battery]].

